<taxonomicName id="E1F8B8664EA98E7264091D1997F31D7E" authorityName="Basilewsky" authorityYear="1953" class="Insecta" family="Carabidae" genus="Brachytachys" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="" order="Coleoptera" pageId="445" pageNumber="446" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="curtulus">
<emphasis id="76D0EC553094CB90A91C69B5DAFB5383" italics="true" pageId="445" pageNumber="446">Brachytachys curtulus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Basilewsky, 1953 by original designation. Synonymy established by Bruneau de 
<normalizedToken id="8CBD66485018CA2CFF0CD9247380FB2A" originalValue="MirÃ©">Mire</normalizedToken>
(1964: 71). Etymology. From the Greek 
<emphasis id="88F65517772F10F4B6B65D5DCA18247A" italics="true" pageId="445" pageNumber="446">brachys</emphasis>
(short) and the generic name 
<taxonomicName id="B6EA47F646E516A864FC1C90820073E3" authorityName="Dejean" authorityYear="1821" class="Hexapoda" family="Carabidae" genus="Tachys" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="" order="Coleoptera" pageId="445" pageNumber="446" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="DBEF06BD2D7DFF21F4231BCABBD96061" italics="true" pageId="445" pageNumber="446">Tachys</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
[
<emphasis id="EECF77B01042991942DB5D7934ECA145" italics="true" pageId="445" pageNumber="446">q.v</emphasis>
.] [masculine].
</paragraph>
