<taxonomicName id="E51554FD5E13789945DA379A1556F038" authorityName="Lucas" authorityYear="1846" class="Insecta" family="Carabidae" genus="Bembidium" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="" order="Coleoptera" pageId="445" pageNumber="446" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="algiricum">
<emphasis id="F151E02D09FF8CC7FDF8102558352D31" italics="true" pageId="445" pageNumber="446">Bembidium algiricum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Lucas, 1846 by original designation. Synonymy established by Lindroth (1966: 424). Etymology. From the Greek 
<emphasis id="5061628C5946F0294D133DF4FB77DD80" italics="true" pageId="445" pageNumber="446">neo</emphasis>
(new) and the generic name 
<taxonomicName id="BE3E13EA6DB9993D187329A37E185646" authorityName="Dejean" authorityYear="1821" class="Hexapoda" family="Carabidae" genus="Tachys" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="" order="Coleoptera" pageId="445" pageNumber="446" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="BB029433EE3D13D205057E71F72DEF7D" italics="true" pageId="445" pageNumber="446">Tachys</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
[
<emphasis id="65EE108745C1403E04F119C10EFEE6B3" italics="true" pageId="445" pageNumber="446">q.v</emphasis>
.] [masculine].
</paragraph>
