Jeannel, 1962: 611. Type species: 
<taxonomicName id="664BE74BD80461A2A21EC1D3BD9CCBD2" authorityName="Jeannel" authorityYear="1962" class="Insecta" family="Carabidae" genus="Polyderidius" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF,CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="" order="Coleoptera" pageId="445" pageNumber="446" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="rapoporti">
<emphasis id="43872F871078B08F3DE1835351853833" italics="true" pageId="445" pageNumber="446">Polyderidius rapoporti</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Jeannel, 1962 by original designation. Synonymy established by Erwin (1974a: 143).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="1DA50AAC6A0535CA17E8BAA21914B8B7" pageId="445" pageNumber="446" type="diversity">
<paragraph id="B580FAF54E148A311D6841EC9891AC76" pageId="445" pageNumber="446">Diversity.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="A1D2D712F8ABCCC9AB1DF18A41563639" pageId="445" pageNumber="446">Worldwide, with about 40 species in the Nearctic (three species), Neotropical (ten species), Australian (nine species), Oriental (eight species), Palaearctic (nine species), and Afrotropical (ten species) Regions. One species is also known from the Hawaiian Islands.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="50633C97546A9A4B4FFFB58068BD3EA6" pageId="445" pageNumber="446" type="identification">
<paragraph id="8709A960846A2FE53166EC9866FF93BA" pageId="445" pageNumber="446">Identification.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8112FFA99E92508A5A8DB195EA5A8C21" pageId="445" pageNumber="446">
Lindroth (1966: 424-427) treated two (
<taxonomicName id="C61ED0915E1BB6418969176A829B4872" baseAuthorityName="Say" baseAuthorityYear="1823" class="Hexapoda" family="Carabidae" genus="Polyderis" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="" order="Coleoptera" pageId="445" pageNumber="446" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="laeva">
<emphasis id="E2C25D993B521EE0AFBA448C1A08FAC2" italics="true" pageId="445" pageNumber="446">Polyderis laeva</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="3C6AF1097FB94E35D0FC8B3570FFFE89" baseAuthorityName="Hayward" baseAuthorityYear="1900" class="Hexapoda" family="Carabidae" genus="Polyderis" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="" order="Coleoptera" pageId="445" pageNumber="446" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="rufotestacea">
<emphasis id="98796BCB68777E577404B3BE97AF8F12" italics="true" pageId="445" pageNumber="446">Polyderis rufotestacea</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
) of the three species found in North America.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="E82C89710B8075071E55C77A4B5CA95F" pageId="445" pageNumber="446" type="taxonomic note">
<paragraph id="848E03C2B994A7AD79F55955400913E5" pageId="445" pageNumber="446">Taxonomic Note.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="E4E6AC91C1E8A3E58E51DA4997728630" pageId="445" pageNumber="446">
This taxon is considered a subgenus of 
<taxonomicName id="DC494582B2D8D60A4DE77C39A6F895C0" authorityName="Dejean" authorityYear="1821" class="Hexapoda" family="Carabidae" genus="Tachys" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="" order="Coleoptera" pageId="445" pageNumber="446" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="0CC51C33FBAE12D376394EFD165F2E58" italics="true" pageId="445" pageNumber="446">Tachys</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by some authors (e.g., Lorenz 2005: 211).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
